cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a novel object localization methodology using a convolutional neural network architecture, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on improving the accuracy of object detection systems, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of conditional probabilities and probabilistic frameworks suggests a potential connection to neural networks and probabilistic models (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the PASCAL VOC2007 dataset, which is a common benchmark in multimedia (cs.MM).
